ng%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EChandrayaan-3%20Mission%3A%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnAnaglyph%20is%20a%20simple%20visualization%20of%20the%20object%20or%20terrain%20in%20three%20dimensions%20from%20stereo%20or%20multi-view%20images.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20Anaglyph%20presented%20here%20is%20created%20using%20NavCam%20Stereo%20Images%2C%20which%20consist%20of%20both%20a%20left%20and%20right%20image%20captured%20onboard%20the%20Pragyan%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FT8ksnvrovA%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FT8ksnvrovA%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20ISRO%20(%40isro)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fisro%2Fstatus%2F1699039768053706764%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ESeptember%205%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnaglyph%20is%20a%20simple%20visualization%20of%20an%20object%20or%20terrain%20in%20three%20dimensions%20from%20stereo%20or%20multi-view%20images.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20this%203-channel%20image%2C%20the%20left%20image%20is%20positioned%20in%20the%20red%20channel%2C%20while%20the%20right%20image%20is%20placed%20in%20the%20blue%20and%20green%20channels%20(creating%20cyan).%20The%20difference%20in%20perspective%20between%20these%20two%20images%20results%20in%20the%20stereo%20effect%2C%20which%20gives%20the%20visual%20impression%20of%20three%20dimensions.%20Red%20and%20cyan%20glasses%20are%20recommended%20for%20viewing%20in%203D%2C%26quot%3B%20ISRO%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERed%20and%20cyan%20glasses%20are%20recommended%20for%20viewing%20in%203D.%20NavCam%20was%20developed%20by%20LEOS%2FISRO.%20Data%20processing%20is%20carried%20out%20by%20SAC%2FISRO%2C%20the%20space%20agency%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693977780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2F9shajc98_chandrayaan3-lander-is-in-the-center-of-the-image_625x300_06_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fnasa-posts-pic-of-chandrayaan-3-lander-on-moon-clicked-by-its-